<title>NEW ZEALAND: Peters sees no big cut likely in NZ 1998 surplus.</title>
<headline>Peters sees no big cut likely in NZ 1998 surplus.</headline>
<dateline>WELLINGTON 1997-06-26</dateline>
<text>
<p>Treasurer Winston Peters said he did not expect a similar large, last-minute reduction in the surplus next year as this year.</p>
<p>Between the Budget Policy Statement in March and the Budget the surplus for 1997/98 was revised down from NZ$3.3 billion to $1.5 billion.</p>
<p>Asked if he was confident a similar revision would not occur next year Peters said: &quot;I certainly don't believe so.&quot;</p>
